3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo calculates funding rates every hour based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices, with rates applied at settlement intervals. The platform's off-chain order book aggregates funding rate data while maintaining on-chain settlement security. Funding payments occur between long and short position holders, with the rollup's low latency enabling precise rate tracking for ADA/USDT positions."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ADA","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ADA/USDT represents significant L1 blockchain exposure with substantial trading volume, making it ideal for funding rate strategies. Cardano's established market position generates consistent funding rate patterns, while the USDT pairing provides stable collateral for arbitrage positions."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical ADA Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ADA/USDT funding rates on Aevo typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% during normal market conditions, with spikes during Cardano ecosystem developments. Network upgrades and DeFi protocol launches often create temporary funding rate imbalances lasting 12-48 hours. The 1-hour funding interval allows traders to capture short-term rate movements more frequently than 8-hour systems. Correlation analysis shows ADA funding rates often diverge from Bitcoin during Cardano-specific news cycles."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities on Aevo"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's combined options-perps platform enables sophisticated arbitrage strategies beyond simple funding rate capture. Traders can hedge ADA perpetual positions with Cardano options while collecting funding payments, creating delta-neutral income streams. The platform's rollup architecture provides faster execution for time-sensitive funding rate arbitrage compared to mainnet DEXs. Cross-platform arbitrage opportunities exist when Aevo's ADA funding rates diverge significantly from centralized exchanges."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's smaller liquidity pool compared to major centralized exchanges can create slippage risks during large arbitrage positions. The rollup's centralization concerns require monitoring of validator uptime and potential bridge risks for USDT collateral. Funding rate volatility during Cardano network events can create unexpected losses if positions aren't properly hedged. The platform's complex product set may create liquidation risks when combining perpetual and options strategies."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical ADA/USDT funding rates on Aevo?","answer":"ADA funding rates on Aevo generally range from -0.05% to +0.15% hourly, with higher volatility during Cardano ecosystem developments. The 1-hour funding interval provides more frequent rate adjustments compared to traditional 8-hour systems."},{"question":"How does Aevo's rollup affect ADA arbitrage execution?","answer":"Aevo's dedicated rollup provides faster settlement times for ADA positions, typically under 1 second for most trades. This speed advantage enables more precise funding rate arbitrage timing, especially when rates change rapidly during market volatility."},{"question":"Can I combine ADA options with perpetual funding strategies?","answer":"Yes, Aevo's integrated platform allows combining ADA options with perpetual positions for enhanced arbitrage strategies. Traders can hedge delta exposure with options while maintaining funding rate collection from perpetual positions."},{"question":"What liquidity considerations affect ADA/USDT funding arbitrage?","answer":"Aevo's ADA/USDT pair has moderate liquidity compared to major centralized exchanges, requiring careful position sizing to minimize slippage. Large arbitrage positions may need to be split across multiple intervals to avoid market impact."}]}]
